ights acquisitions and land development behavior, Planning Forum, vol.7, pp.21-27.75.Lai, S. K. (2008), Economic Impacts of Compensation Policies of Agricultural Land Acquisition in China: A Property Rights Approach, AsRES.76.Lai, W. C. and Hung, W. Y. (2008), The inner logic of the Coase Theorem and a Coasian planning research agenda, Environment and Planning B: Planning and Design, Vol.35, pp.207-226.77.Stigler, G. J. (1972), The Law and Economics of Public Policy: A Plea to the Scholar, Journal of Legal Studies, Vol.1.78.Tang, B. S.,Wong, S. W. and Liu, S. C. (2006), Property Agents, Housing Markets and Housing Services in Transitional Urban China, Housing Studies, Vol.21, No.6, pp.799-823.79.Wu, F. and Yeh, A. G. O. (1996), The new land development process and urban development in Chinese cities. International Journal of Urban and regional Research, 20.2, pp.330-353.五、英文書籍80.Arrow(1969), The Organization of Economic Activity：Issues Pertinent to the Choice of Market versus Non-Market Allocation, In The Analysis and Evalution of Public Expenditures, Government Printing Office.81.Barzel, Y. (1999), Economic analysis of property rights, Cambridge University Press.82.Benham, A. and Benhan, L. (2004), The Cost of Exchange: An Approach to Measuring Transaction Costs. Working paper.83.Williamson, O. W.(1987),Kenneth Arrow and the New Institutional Economics,in Arrow and the Foundation of the Theory of Economics Policy, ed.by Feiwel,G.R.,New York University Press.










